I"W<p>I haven‚Äôt written a post in quite a while, so I decided to document my failure to come up with a viable alternative to the translatable animations we use in <a href="https://help.gnome.org/users/gnome-help/3.18/getting-started.html.en">Getting Started</a> documentation. So let‚Äôs start with what‚Äôs wrong with it. Despite being far more maintainable than a screencast, it‚Äôs still a major hassle to keep the videos in sync with the developing designs. Every translation requires a re-render of all the frames and it quickly grows into gigabytes per language.</p>

