<h1 id="css">CSS</h1>

<p>A much more appealing was the concept of using CSS animation. We do a lot of transitions and some animation in gtk+, so it would have been great to reuse the same technology here. While CSS transitions are spot on, animation with a sense of a global timeline is not really the use case for the web. Usually animation in the intended context is an individual transform happening after an event triggered. Creating a sequence of various objects animating in a global timeline is pretty awkward. Especially if you want to loop the whole animation infinitely. The only tools for your disposal is either a time offset or relative time keyframes, keeping all objects‚Äô animation the same length.</p>

